result.adr_address: 45號 Tai Hong St, Aldrich Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 45號 Tai Hong St, Aldrich Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Mint & Basil

reviews.text: This is actually quite a nice venue, facing the harbor - its a great place to chill and enjoy a Sunday lunch. The food was actually quite good, however, unfortunately, none of it came in the order it should have. Appetizers came after the main course and the vegetables arrived after everything else had been finished. The food was good, but for the money, the service was very disappointing and, even after we'd pointed the lack of attention to detail out to the individual I'm assuming either owns or manages it, we were met with a quite indifference that suggested our comments weren't justified, even though we had to remind them at least twice that we hadn't received the vegetables we'd ordered...

Very helpful & Friendly resturant because that day I will my Friend bring three doggy but they're immediately open the chairs for doggy so smart! 
And the food very delicious & advice dessert deep fired banana so nice with Honey to ate!

I recommend the chicken curry rice. The lunch menu is also very good and not expensive as per Hong Kong standards. The personel is very friendly.
If you are sensitive to the view it is interesting from there.
Food was good, but considered pricey given the quality. The drinks were good though, ordered a strawberry martini and it was very smooth

Lovely place and great food. Shame they don't cater a bit better for vegetarians. They will cook a vegetarian version of the Pad Thai and other noodle dishes if you ask (and are very good at checking whether egg is ok or not) But the menu doesn't show it as options which is disappointing - and also means you can't order from them on deliveroo etc. Service can be a bit slow sometimes, and dishes never come out at the same time.
Comfortable living environment and convenient to travel around
